  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Line a bamboo tray or 9x13-inch baking dish with parchment paper.",
    "In a medium bowl, whisk together the egg yolks, granulated sweetener, and vanilla extract.",
    "In a separate bowl, mix together the breadcrumbs and Korean chili flakes.",
    "Dip each pre-fried teque os piece into the breadcrumb mixture, coating both sides evenly.",
    "Place the coated teque os pieces on the prepared tray or baking dish in a single layer.",
    "Drizzle the heavy cream over the top of the teque os pieces.",
    "Dot the top of the cream with the unsalted butter.",
    "Sprinkle the Italian parsley over the top of the dish.",
    "Bake for 20 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the cream is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before serving."
  ],
